cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV

This paper proposes a neural network architecture for learning word-referent associations in multiple contexts, which involves processing raw images and streams of phonemes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also mentions the use of a Self-Organizing Map, which is a type of unsupervised learning algorithm commonly used in neural networks, suggesting that the paper could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the accuracy and learning rates of the proposed model, indicating that it could be relevant to cs.LG (Learning). The use of image processing also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper proposes a biologically inspired architecture, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
